3. Role Updates — Validation Message Consistency

---

Affected endpoint: `PUT /api/admin/users`

Changes made:

* Updated validation error message to include `public` role
* Ensured allowed roles list matches:
  * `['public', 'staff', 'admin']`
* Added safety check for missing `user_type_id` lookup before update

Behavior breakdown:

| Scenario                  | Before                                | After                                      |
| ------------------------- | ------------------------------------- | ------------------------------------------ |
| Updating to public role   | Allowed but message inconsistent      | Fully consistent validation + messaging     |
| Invalid role input        | Message omitted "public"              | Message includes all valid roles            |
| Missing role in DB        | Could silently fail                   | Now explicitly handled                     |

